        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Roth IRA contributions are subject to income phase-out limits set by the IRS, which change annually. If your Modified Adjusted Gross Income (MAGI) exceeds the limit for your filing status, your allowed contribution decreases or phases out completely. High earners can still use a strategy known as a 'Backdoor Roth IRA' to contribute."
      }
    },
