      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can I withdraw my money from a Roth IRA before retirement?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "You can withdraw your direct contributions to a Roth IRA at any time, for any reason, without taxes or penalties, because you have already paid taxes on that money. However, withdrawing investment earnings before age 59½ typically incurs taxes and a 10% penalty, unless you qualify for specific exemptions like a first-time home purchase."
      }
